  <config controlweight="0.5">
<documentation>SERIAL PROTOCOL:
Baud rate: 19200 (Bits per second)
Data bits: 8bits
Parity: None
Stop bits: 1bit

A DB9 to Mini 8-Pin cable is required to connect projector to the controller using this pin configuration:
Controller-Pin2 &gt;&gt; Projector Pin6
Controller-Pin3 &gt;&gt; Projector Pin1
Controller-Pin5 &gt;&gt; Projector Pin4
Controller-Pin5 &gt;&gt; Projector Pin7
Controller-Pin5 &gt;&gt; Projector Pin8
Controller-Pin7 &gt;&gt; Projector Pin5
Controller-Pin8 &gt;&gt; Projector Pin5

PROJECT VARIABLES &amp; EVENTS:
VARIABLE NAME &lt;&lt;&gt;&gt; EVENT NAME [VARIABLE TYPE, (VALUES)]

Lamp_Number &lt;&lt;&gt;&gt; Lamp_Number_Changed [NUMBER, (Lamp number)]

Lamp_Time_Actual &lt;&lt;&gt;&gt; Lamp_Time_Actual_Changed [NUMBER, (Running time of lamp by hours)]

Lamp_Time_Correspondingl &lt;&lt;&gt;&gt; Lamp_Time_Corresponding_Changed [NUMBER, (Running time of lamp by hours - corresponding value, not actual running time)]

Lamp_Replacement_Time &lt;&lt;&gt;&gt; Lamp_Replacement_Time_Changed [STRING, (YES = Over lamp replacement time, NO = Within lamp replacement time)]

Lamp_Mode_Status &lt;&lt;&gt;&gt; Lamp_Mode_Status_Changed [STRING, (HIGH = Lamp Mode is High, AUTO = Lamp Mode is Auto, NORMAL=  Lamp Mode is Normal)]

Lamp_Lighting_Status &lt;&lt;&gt;&gt; Lamp_Lighting_Status_Changed [STRING, (ON, OFF, FAILURE)]

Projector_Running_Time &lt;&lt;&gt;&gt; Projector_Running_Time_Changed [NUMBER, (Running time of projector by hours)]

Projector_Operating_Status &lt;&lt;&gt;&gt; Projector_Operating_Status_Changed [NUMBER, (See list below.)]
POWER_ON
STANDBY
STANDBY_AFTER_LAMP_FAILURE
POWER_SAVE
POWER_FAILURE
COUNTDOWN
COOLING_DOWN
COOLING_DOWN_POWER_SAVE
COOLING_DOWN_LAMP_FAILURE
COOLING_DOWN_TEMPERATURE_ANOMALY
RECOVERY_FROM_TEMPERATURE_ANOMALY




PROJECTOR CONFIGURATION:
The Input Search must be set to 'OFF' in the projector's setup menu. Since Input Search attempts to detect an input signal automatically, the Power Off sequence may be disrupted if this feature is enabled. 

This is caused when the source component has powered down and no input is presented to the projector. In this scenario, the projector will begin to cylce inputs, disrutpting the Power Off sequence.

</documentation>
